<p><b>What movie is based on Foster?</b> Based on the renowned story, Foster, by Claire Keegan, THE QUIET GIRL is an exquisite and heart-wrenching Irish drama set in 1981.</p>
<p><b>What secret is revealed in Foster?</b> It is only then that she discovers the big unspoken secret at the heart of the story: the Kinsellas had a young son who drowned tragically in the slurry pit and she has been wearing his clothes since she arrived at their house.</p>
<p><b>What is the true story behind Foster Boy?</b> “Foster Boy” is based on the work of Chicago attorney Jay Paul Deratany, who for 20 years has been fighting on behalf of children abused or killed while under the care of private foster care firms contracted by state child welfare agencies, beginning with Illinois. Starring Matthew Modine, Louis Gossett Jr.</p>
